{"kind":"article","sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-244-Efficient-Interactions-with-Frameworks","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true}]},{"level":2,"text":"Related Sessions","type":"heading","anchor":"Related-Sessions"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-212-Whats-New-in-Foundation","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-402-Whats-New-in-Swift","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-416-Understanding-Swift-Performance"],"style":"list","type":"links"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Border crossings can be smooth and efficient or slow and tedious. The boundary between an app and a framework is analogous, but inefficiencies may not always be obvious. Whether it’s passing data to an API or understanding how to stay on the fast path while rendering text, we’ll explore various aspects of how an app can work efficiently with underlying frameworks. If you build your own frameworks, gain valuable insights into how your clients can be as efficient as possible.","type":"text"}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/244\/","overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","isActive":true}},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-244-efficient-interactions-with-frameworks"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC17","role":"sampleCode","title":"Efficient Interactions with Frameworks"},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-416-Understanding-Swift-Performance":{"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","title":"Understanding Swift Performance","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-416-understanding-swift-performance","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-416-Understanding-Swift-Performance","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In this advanced session, find out how structs, classes, protocols, and generics are implemented in Swift. Learn about their relative costs in different dimensions of performance. See how to apply this information to speed up your code."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-402-Whats-New-in-Swift":{"role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-402-Whats-New-in-Swift","type":"topic","title":"What’s New in Swift","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-402-whats-new-in-swift","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift 4 continues the evolution of the safe, fast, and expressive language, with better performance and new features. Learn about the new String and improved generics, see how Swift 4 maintains support for your existing Swift 3 code, and get insight into where Swift is headed in the future."}]},"WWDC17-Icon.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-Icon.png"}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"type":"link","title":"Learn More…","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2017/244/":{"url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/244\/","checksum":null,"type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/244\/"},"WWDC17.jpeg":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"WWDCNotes.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"title":"WWDC17","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg","type":"card"}],"role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17","abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"New APIs: ","type":"text"},{"code":"Core NFC","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and more.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-212-Whats-New-in-Foundation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-212-Whats-New-in-Foundation","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Whether you’re building apps for iOS, macOS, watchOS, or tvOS, a lot of the functionality you get from Apple’s SDKs comes from the Foundation framework. Join the Foundation engineering team to hear about the improvements they’ve been working on. Learn how significant changes to key paths can help make your code safer with strong type checking in Swift. Hear all about how the new archiving API can help you safely convert your native Swift types to and from external formats like JSON.  Gain insights into performance enhancements that will help make your app even more efficient."}],"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-212-whats-new-in-foundation","type":"topic","title":"What’s New in Foundation"}}}